    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once beginning to soften, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong>, <strong>diced potato </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>to the dish and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>drained cannellini beans</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>bay leaf<span class=\"text-danger\">[ves]</span></strong>, <strong>dried thyme </strong>and <strong>duck jelly</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>red wine paste</strong>, <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[550ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
