        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash, then rip the leaves off the <strong>spring greens</strong>, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and slice into thin strips</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced spring greens</strong> to a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Scrunch the foil around the spring greens to form a tightly sealed parcel, add to a baking tray and set aside (this will go in the oven later!)</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Make 2 separate parcels!</p>",
      "order": 6,
